			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="3095">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p><strong>The Sun</strong> arrived yesterday with John Gatto&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/937">Why Schools Don&rsquo;t Educate</a>&rdquo; [Issue 175]. It&rsquo;s a very important document and I am grateful for it.</p>

<p>As a teacher of young children I especially respond to his statements about the lack of time in schooling. One can see the bewilderment in the eyes of students as they are forced to change activities or move faster than their own sense of time suggests. And I join John Gatto in being offended by the school&rsquo;s intrusion into the privacy of children. Most of all, I appreciate Gatto&rsquo;s emphasis on <em>family</em> as a vital element of true education. Each September I tell my students&rsquo; parents, &ldquo;I couldn&rsquo;t do it without you,&rdquo; and I mean it. Our relationship is critical to their child&rsquo;s sense of self and community.</p>

<p>The one area Gatto did not touch on directly, and which I feel needs greater attention, concerns our disappearing notion of childhood. It is so subtle it often goes unrecognized. Neil Postman has spoken to this point in <em>The Disappearance Of Childhood</em>, as has David Elkind in <em>The Harried Child</em>,<em> All Grown Up And No Place To Go: Teen-Agers In Crisis</em>, and <em>Miseducation</em>.</p>

<p>May I please have permission to copy the article so it can aid reflection, dialogue, and action on behalf of children and the larger community?</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Juaneva Smith<br>Quathiaski Cove, British Columbia<br />Canada</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
		<div class="cta cta-l1" data-url="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">
			<div class="cta-intro">
				<h5 class="cta-title alt-ff">Thinking about writing us a letter?</h5>
				<p class="cta-text">Give in to the temptation. We love getting mail. <br><span class="xsmall">(Of course, we reserve the right to edit.)</span></p>
			</div>
			<a href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor" class="cta-button b b-4 b-padding-tight small" data-label="Write Us A Letter!">Write Us A Letter!</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	

